2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: Part one of a new storyline and a great jumping-on point for new readers! Jeff Lemire returns as regular artist for part one of "Unnatural Habits." While Jeppard, Singh and Gus make plans to head to Alaska, things start to deteriorate for the rest of the group back at the sanctuary in the dam. Plus: a variant cover by ANIMAL MAN artist Travel Foreman!
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: Unnatural Habitats

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description:
In the wake of the ‘Second Coming’ saga, a new X-Force is created! Wolverine and Deadpool are joined by Archangel, Psylocke and Fantomex – and their first mission is to stop the rebirth of Apocalypse! Don’t miss the start of a dark new era!

Also: Deadpool meets the Secret Avengers!

Includes material reprinted from X-Force #1-2 and Deadpool #27.
Translates Green Lantern #66-67, Green Lantern Corps #60 & Green Lantern: Emerald Warriors #10-12.

The Utopia and Gen Hope teens have come to the Academy as prisoners? Sebastian Shaw strikes! Guest-starring Wolverine, Hawkeye, Hercules and Captain America!

Note: Sentinel Mark IV only appears on the cover.
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: Protective Services, Part 1

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: ONE OF MTV’S “TEN BEST ON-GOING COMIC BOOK SERIES OF 2011!” With the Plutonian back on Earth, Max has faced countless trials that test his ability to remain inflexibly focused on the cause of justice. But Max’s greatest test is yet to come, and no one in the INCORRUPTIBLE universe will be the same. Don’t miss this thrilling issue in the companion to Mark Waid’s Eisner-nominated superhero series, IRREDEEMABLE!

When all of her decisions turn out for the worse, and with a young boy's life in danger, it's up to Pixie to save the day. However, she's faced with a Skrull bent on vengeance with some powerful weapons at his disposal.

Empress Sonja has renounced her throne and returns to Sogoria with her rightful spoils, but curiously the road home passes close to Tirket and the holy Temples of the Way. With Koliostri elsewhere trying to claim the Emoran throne she left behind, Sonja find a detour is in order.

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description:
To prevent a death the Secret Avengers must risk starting a war!

A secret romance heats up!

A rivalry between two members threatens to jeopardize the mission!

Will Hawkeye discover he has a spy on his team in time to prevent tragedy?
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: A Council of Masters

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: Skinner Sweet is back! And he’s hunting Hollywood vampires in 1954. But how did he survive the horrible events of Taipan back in WWII? Unlikely alliances are formed, secrets are revealed, and another name gets crossed off “The Blacklist” as the next major AMERICAN VAMPIRE epic roars on!
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: The Blacklist, Part Two of Six

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description:
AVX TIE-IN!

They gather to stop the horrors of the Marvel universe before they happen…

…but the secret group known as the Illuminati failed to stop the Phoenix time and time again.

They come together one last time…but will it be enough?
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: Illuminati Assemble

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: The Nu-Gene terrorist group known as The Quanta have gone and pissed of Bloodstrike, And when that happens, the only way out is in pieces. BLOODSTRIKE creator ROB LIEFELD lends his dynamic art to a tale of revenge and the costs of retaliation.
It's all built to this: FINAL EXECUTION enters its last act! The new Brotherhood of Evil Mutants makes their move as Fantomex's deceptions come back to haunt the team!
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: No Trust in Tomorrow

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description:
The Avengers versus the unbelievable might of the X-Men!

The special issue of Avengers is the flip side to Wolverine and the X-Men #12.

Witness a very surprising tie-in experience like you’ve never seen before!

Editor's Note: This story takes place concurrent with the events of Wolverine and the X-Men #11 and before the events of AvX #8.
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: Avengers Ambush!

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: On the way to the Dark Moon wrap party Kyoko bumps into her cast mate Kijima. He’s never paid her any attention before, but he heard that people called her beautiful when they saw her in her Natsu role. Kijima can’t contain his curiosity and buys Kyoko a total makeover for the party. But is his interest innocent, or does he have wicked plans in store?!

Part two of the ARMS RACE arc finds Green Hornet and Kato battling an all-out assault from an imported villain seeking to wipe out all competition and make Century City his own.
There is only one warrior Glory has ever feared; only one who's more dangerous than her, only one she knows can stop her. Get ready for the coming of Nanaja, Glory's little sister.
2012-01-01|2012-12-30.name: Bloodshadow, Part One: In Revolt

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: Four fabulous guys must completely transform a high school into a real lady if they want to go on living rent-free in her aunt's luxurious mansion. But the girl turns out to be Sunako, the most fashion-hopeless girl in Japan, who'd rather live like a hermit and watch her favorite horror movies than undergo a makeover!

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: Bruce Wayne successfully courted the attention of Abbatoir 2, leaving him at the mercy of a killer. Of course, Batman doesn't need anyone to rescue him...but will Jim Gordon and the GCPD discover some uncomfortable facts when they investigate the case? "Off the Menu" part 3 of 3.

2012-01-01|2012-12-30.description: Anything boys can do, girls can do better! The gals are taking center stage and showing the boys who's boss! Watch the girls as they challenge their male counterparts to a dance-off, show them what's what on the sports field and even fight crime! It's not just a battle of the sexes, but also a fun walk through history, highlighting important female figures throughout time, standing up for what's right! This 100+ page digital exclusive features the lovely ladies of Riverdale, including Betty, Veronica, Nancy, Cheryl, Ethel, Ginger, Trula Twyst and Brigitte! In this collection, the girls really do rule!
